fcombinat

A C library and command-line tool for generic (un)ranking of
combinatorial structures. Given a formal specification in the symbolic method,
fcombinat derives ranking and unranking algorithms automatically, with no
hand-crafted code per structure. Compatible with specification files from the
ECS-data repository (Jeremy Lumbroso).

BUILDING
    Dependencies: gcc, bison, flex, flint, libm

    make

    The binary is placed at ./fcombinat.
    To use a different compiler: make CC=clang

USAGE
    fcombinat [OPTIONS] ACTION -n N

DESCRIPTION
    Parses a combinatorial specification (grammar) and performs ranking,
    unranking, enumeration, or series expansion. Implements generic ranking and
    unranking algorithms for both labeled and unlabeled structures, based on the
    Molinero et al. framework. Unlabeled Cycle ranking remains an open problem
    and is not yet supported.

OPTIONS
    -j, -g, --parse-json <FILE|SPEC>
            Path to a JSON grammar specification file, or an inline spec string.

    -n, --size <N>
            Size parameter. Required for all actions.

    -l, --labeled
            Treat the specification as a labeled combinatorial class (EGF semantics).
            Without this flag, OGF semantics are used.

    -P, --poly
            Output terms in polynomial format (e.g., c*z^n).

    -v, --verbose
            Enable verbose output.

    --symbol <S>
            Target symbol to analyze or generate.
            If not provided, the first symbol in the grammar is used.

    --order <lex|boustrophedon>
            Ranking order used by --rank, --unrank, --enum-all, and --bijection.
            Default: lex.

            lex             Canonical lexicographic order derived from the
                            combinatorial number system (default).

            boustrophedon   Boustrophedonic order: at each level of the
                            combinatorial decomposition tree, the enumeration
                            direction alternates (even depths go left-to-right,
                            odd depths go right-to-left). The same set of objects
                            is produced as with lex; only the bijection changes.

ACTIONS (mutually exclusive, one required)
    --terms
            Print coefficients c_0..c_N of the generating function.

    --rank <OBJ>
            Compute the integer rank of the given object string in the
            chosen --order (default: lex).

    --unrank <INT>
            Generate the object at the given integer rank in the
            chosen --order (default: lex).

    --enum-all
            Enumerate and print all objects of size N.

    --bijection
            Run rank -> unrank -> rank roundtrip tests for sizes 1..N-1.
            Exhaustive when c_n <= 50, sampled otherwise.
            Requires --symbol.

EXAMPLES
    # Print the first 6 coefficients (Catalan numbers, unlabeled binary trees)
    fcombinat -j "{T = Union(Z, Prod(T, T))}" -n 5 --terms

    # Unrank the 13th labeled binary tree of size 4
    fcombinat -j bintrees.json -n 4 --labeled --unrank 13

    # Rank a specific object
    fcombinat -j "{T = Union(Z, Prod(T, T))}" -n 4 --unrank 3 | \
      xargs -I{} fcombinat -j "{T = Union(Z, Prod(T, T))}" -n 4 --rank "{}"

    # Bijection test on permutations (labeled)
    fcombinat -j "{P = Set(Cycle(Z))}" -n 6 --labeled --symbol P --bijection

    # Bijection test using boustrophedon order
    fcombinat -j "{P = Set(Cycle(Z))}" -n 6 --labeled --symbol P --bijection --order boustrophedon

    # Enumerate all unlabeled integer partitions of size 5 in boustrophedon order
    fcombinat -j "{P = Set(Sequence(Z, card >= 1))}" -n 5 --enum-all --order boustrophedon

TESTING
    Requires the ecs-data submodule (git submodule update --init).

    make test              # counting: compare first 10 coefficients (1075 specs)
    make test-bijection    # bijection roundtrip (lex order): all 1075 specs
    make test-bijection-boustrophedon  # bijection roundtrip (boustrophedon): all 1075 specs
    make test-unique       # uniqueness: no duplicate objects up to depth 5
    make                   # all phases in parallel

    Failures are printed immediately and logged to test_errors.log.
    Each phase prints a single summary line on completion; passing tests are silent.

    Configuration (config.mk):
        NTERMS      number of terms to verify     (default: 10)
        ENUM_DEPTH  max size for uniqueness test   (default: 5)

BENCHMARKS
    Measures CPU cycles for count/rank/unrank across several combinatorial structures.
    Optionally compares against Maple (CAS) if available.

    make bench

    Results are written to exp/performance/results/ as CSV files.

    Configuration (config.mk):
        FCOMBINAT_BIN  path to the fcombinat binary  (default: ./fcombinat)
        MAPLE_BIN      path to the Maple binary       (default: ~/maple2026/bin/maple)

FIGURES
    Generates bar-chart PDFs from the latest benchmark results.
    Requires latexmk and a TeX distribution with pgfplots.

    make figures       # rebuild all PDFs in exp/perf-operations/
    make clean-figures # remove generated PDFs and TeX artifacts

REPOSITORY LAYOUT
    src/               C source (grammar, solver, API/CLI)
    include/           Public headers
    exp/
      correctness/     ECS-based correctness test suite
      performance/     Benchmark runner and results
      perf-operations/ Figure generation (reshape + LaTeX)
    config.mk          Binary paths and tuning knobs
